6747 namespace {
6748 class ARMPipelinerLoopInfo : public TargetInstrInfo::PipelinerLoopInfo {
6749  MachineInstr *EndLoop, *LoopCount;
6750  MachineFunction *MF;
6751  const TargetInstrInfo *TII;
6752 
6753  // Bitset[0 .. MAX_STAGES-1] ... iterations needed
6754  // [LAST_IS_USE] : last reference to register in schedule is a use
6755  // [SEEN_AS_LIVE] : Normal pressure algorithm believes register is live
6756  static int constexpr MAX_STAGES = 30;
6757  static int constexpr LAST_IS_USE = MAX_STAGES;
6758  static int constexpr SEEN_AS_LIVE = MAX_STAGES + 1;
6759  typedef std::bitset<MAX_STAGES + 2> IterNeed;
6760  typedef std::map<unsigned, IterNeed> IterNeeds;
6761 
6762  void bumpCrossIterationPressure(RegPressureTracker &RPT,
6763  const IterNeeds &CIN);
6764  bool tooMuchRegisterPressure(SwingSchedulerDAG &SSD, SMSchedule &SMS);
6765 
6766  // Meanings of the various stuff with loop types:
6767  // t2Bcc:
6768  // EndLoop = branch at end of original BB that will become a kernel
6769  // LoopCount = CC setter live into branch
6770  // t2LoopEnd:
6771  // EndLoop = branch at end of original BB
6772  // LoopCount = t2LoopDec
6773 public:
6774  ARMPipelinerLoopInfo(MachineInstr *EndLoop, MachineInstr *LoopCount)
6775  : EndLoop(EndLoop), LoopCount(LoopCount),
6776  MF(EndLoop->getParent()->getParent()),
6777  TII(MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()) {}
6778 
6779  bool shouldIgnoreForPipelining(const MachineInstr *MI) const override {
6780  // Only ignore the terminator.
6781  return MI == EndLoop || MI == LoopCount;
6782  }
6783 
6784  bool shouldUseSchedule(SwingSchedulerDAG &SSD, SMSchedule &SMS) override {
6785  if (tooMuchRegisterPressure(SSD, SMS))
6786  return false;
6787 
6788  return true;
6789  }
6790 
6791  std::optional<bool> createTripCountGreaterCondition(
6792  int TC, MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
6793  SmallVectorImpl<MachineOperand> &Cond) override {
6794 
6795  if (isCondBranchOpcode(EndLoop->getOpcode())) {
6796  Cond.push_back(EndLoop->getOperand(1));
6797  Cond.push_back(EndLoop->getOperand(2));
6798  if (EndLoop->getOperand(0).getMBB() == EndLoop->getParent()) {
6799  TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond);
6800  }
6801  return {};
6802  } else if (EndLoop->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEnd) {
6803  // General case just lets the unrolled t2LoopDec do the subtraction and
6804  // therefore just needs to check if zero has been reached.
6805  MachineInstr *LoopDec = nullptr;
6806  for (auto &I : MBB.instrs())
6807  if (I.getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopDec)
6808  LoopDec = &I;
6809  assert(LoopDec && "Unable to find copied LoopDec");
6810  // Check if we're done with the loop.
6811  BuildMI(&MBB, LoopDec->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::t2CMPri))
6812  .addReg(LoopDec->getOperand(0).getReg())
6813  .addImm(0)
6814  .addImm(ARMCC::AL)
6815  .addReg(ARM::NoRegister);
6816  Cond.push_back(MachineOperand::CreateImm(ARMCC::EQ));
6817  Cond.push_back(MachineOperand::CreateReg(ARM::CPSR, false));
6818  return {};
6819  } else
6820  llvm_unreachable("Unknown EndLoop");
6821  }
6822 
6823  void setPreheader(MachineBasicBlock *NewPreheader) override {}
6824 
6825  void adjustTripCount(int TripCountAdjust) override {}
6826 
6827  void disposed() override {}
6828 };
6829 
6830 void ARMPipelinerLoopInfo::bumpCrossIterationPressure(RegPressureTracker &RPT,
6831  const IterNeeds &CIN) {
6832  // Increase pressure by the amounts in CrossIterationNeeds
6833  for (const auto &N : CIN) {
6834  int Cnt = N.second.count() - N.second[SEEN_AS_LIVE] * 2;
6835  for (int I = 0; I < Cnt; ++I)
6836  RPT.increaseRegPressure(Register(N.first), LaneBitmask::getNone(),
6837  LaneBitmask::getAll());
6838  }
6839  // Decrease pressure by the amounts in CrossIterationNeeds
6840  for (const auto &N : CIN) {
6841  int Cnt = N.second.count() - N.second[SEEN_AS_LIVE] * 2;
6842  for (int I = 0; I < Cnt; ++I)
6843  RPT.decreaseRegPressure(Register(N.first), LaneBitmask::getAll(),
6844  LaneBitmask::getNone());
6845  }
6846 }
6847 
6848 bool ARMPipelinerLoopInfo::tooMuchRegisterPressure(SwingSchedulerDAG &SSD,
6849  SMSchedule &SMS) {
6850  IterNeeds CrossIterationNeeds;
6851 
6852  // Determine which values will be loop-carried after the schedule is
6853  // applied
6854 
6855  for (auto &SU : SSD.SUnits) {
6856  const MachineInstr *MI = SU.getInstr();
6857  int Stg = SMS.stageScheduled(const_cast<SUnit *>(&SU));
6858  for (auto &S : SU.Succs)
6859  if (MI->isPHI() && S.getKind() == SDep::Anti) {
6860  Register Reg = S.getReg();
6861  if (Reg.isVirtual())
6862  CrossIterationNeeds.insert(std::make_pair(Reg.id(), IterNeed()))
6863  .first->second.set(0);
6864  } else if (S.isAssignedRegDep()) {
6865  int OStg = SMS.stageScheduled(S.getSUnit());
6866  if (OStg >= 0 && OStg != Stg) {
6867  Register Reg = S.getReg();
6868  if (Reg.isVirtual())
6869  CrossIterationNeeds.insert(std::make_pair(Reg.id(), IterNeed()))
6870  .first->second |= ((1 << (OStg - Stg)) - 1);
6871  }
6872  }
6873  }
6874 
6875  // Determine more-or-less what the proposed schedule (reversed) is going to
6876  // be; it might not be quite the same because the within-cycle ordering
6877  // created by SMSchedule depends upon changes to help with address offsets and
6878  // the like.
6879  std::vector<SUnit *> ProposedSchedule;
6880  for (int Cycle = SMS.getFinalCycle(); Cycle >= SMS.getFirstCycle(); --Cycle)
6881  for (int Stage = 0, StageEnd = SMS.getMaxStageCount(); Stage <= StageEnd;
6882  ++Stage) {
6883  std::deque<SUnit *> Instrs =
6884  SMS.getInstructions(Cycle + Stage * SMS.getInitiationInterval());
6885  std::sort(Instrs.begin(), Instrs.end(),
6886  [](SUnit *A, SUnit *B) { return A->NodeNum > B->NodeNum; });
6887  for (SUnit *SU : Instrs)
6888  ProposedSchedule.push_back(SU);
6889  }
6890 
6891  // Learn whether the last use/def of each cross-iteration register is a use or
6892  // def. If it is a def, RegisterPressure will implicitly increase max pressure
6893  // and we do not have to add the pressure.
6894  for (auto *SU : ProposedSchedule)
6895  for (ConstMIBundleOperands OperI(*SU->getInstr()); OperI.isValid();
6896  ++OperI) {
6897  auto MO = *OperI;
6898  if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg())
6899  continue;
6900  Register Reg = MO.getReg();
6901  auto CIter = CrossIterationNeeds.find(Reg.id());
6902  if (CIter == CrossIterationNeeds.end() || CIter->second[LAST_IS_USE] ||
6903  CIter->second[SEEN_AS_LIVE])
6904  continue;
6905  if (MO.isDef() && !MO.isDead())
6906  CIter->second.set(SEEN_AS_LIVE);
6907  else if (MO.isUse())
6908  CIter->second.set(LAST_IS_USE);
6909  }
6910  for (auto &CI : CrossIterationNeeds)
6911  CI.second.reset(LAST_IS_USE);
6912 
6913  RegionPressure RecRegPressure;
6914  RegPressureTracker RPTracker(RecRegPressure);
6915  RegisterClassInfo RegClassInfo;
6916  RegClassInfo.runOnMachineFunction(*MF);
6917  RPTracker.init(MF, &RegClassInfo, nullptr, EndLoop->getParent(),
6918  EndLoop->getParent()->end(), false, false);
6919  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
6920 
6921  bumpCrossIterationPressure(RPTracker, CrossIterationNeeds);
6922 
6923  for (auto *SU : ProposedSchedule) {
6924  MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator CurInstI = SU->getInstr();
6925  RPTracker.setPos(std::next(CurInstI));
6926  RPTracker.recede();
6927 
6928  // Track what cross-iteration registers would be seen as live
6929  for (ConstMIBundleOperands OperI(*CurInstI); OperI.isValid(); ++OperI) {
6930  auto MO = *OperI;
6931  if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg())
6932  continue;
6933  Register Reg = MO.getReg();
6934  if (MO.isDef() && !MO.isDead()) {
6935  auto CIter = CrossIterationNeeds.find(Reg.id());
6936  if (CIter != CrossIterationNeeds.end()) {
6937  CIter->second.reset(0);
6938  CIter->second.reset(SEEN_AS_LIVE);
6939  }
6940  }
6941  }
6942  for (auto &S : SU->Preds) {
6943  auto Stg = SMS.stageScheduled(SU);
6944  if (S.isAssignedRegDep()) {
6945  Register Reg = S.getReg();
6946  auto CIter = CrossIterationNeeds.find(Reg.id());
6947  if (CIter != CrossIterationNeeds.end()) {
6948  auto Stg2 = SMS.stageScheduled(const_cast<SUnit *>(S.getSUnit()));
6949  assert(Stg2 <= Stg && "Data dependence upon earlier stage");
6950  if (Stg - Stg2 < MAX_STAGES)
6951  CIter->second.set(Stg - Stg2);
6952  CIter->second.set(SEEN_AS_LIVE);
6953  }
6954  }
6955  }
6956 
6957  bumpCrossIterationPressure(RPTracker, CrossIterationNeeds);
6958  }
6959 
6960  auto &P = RPTracker.getPressure().MaxSetPressure;
6961  for (unsigned I = 0, E = P.size(); I < E; ++I)
6962  if (P[I] > TRI->getRegPressureSetLimit(*MF, I)) {
6963  return true;
6964  }
6965  return false;
6966 }
6967 
6968 } // namespace
6969 
6970 std::unique_ptr<TargetInstrInfo::PipelinerLoopInfo>
6971 ARMBaseInstrInfo::analyzeLoopForPipelining(MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB) const {
6972  MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = LoopBB->getFirstTerminator();
6973  MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = *LoopBB->pred_begin();
6974  if (Preheader == LoopBB)
6975  Preheader = *std::next(LoopBB->pred_begin());
6976 
6977  if (I != LoopBB->end() && I->getOpcode() == ARM::t2Bcc) {
6978  // If the branch is a Bcc, then the CPSR should be set somewhere within the
6979  // block. We need to determine the reaching definition of CPSR so that
6980  // it can be marked as non-pipelineable, allowing the pipeliner to force
6981  // it into stage 0 or give up if it cannot or will not do so.
6982  MachineInstr *CCSetter = nullptr;
6983  for (auto &L : LoopBB->instrs()) {
6984  if (L.isCall())
6985  return nullptr;
6986  if (isCPSRDefined(L))
6987  CCSetter = &L;
6988  }
6989  if (CCSetter)
6990  return std::make_unique<ARMPipelinerLoopInfo>(&*I, CCSetter);
6991  else
6992  return nullptr; // Unable to find the CC setter, so unable to guarantee
6993  // that pipeline will work
6994  }
6995 
6996  // Recognize:
6997  // preheader:
6998  // %1 = t2DoopLoopStart %0
6999  // loop:
7000  // %2 = phi %1, <not loop>, %..., %loop
7001  // %3 = t2LoopDec %2, <imm>
7002  // t2LoopEnd %3, %loop
7003 
7004  if (I != LoopBB->end() && I->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEnd) {
7005  for (auto &L : LoopBB->instrs())
7006  if (L.isCall())
7007  return nullptr;
7008  else if (isVCTP(&L))
7009  return nullptr;
7010  Register LoopDecResult = I->getOperand(0).getReg();
7011  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = LoopBB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
7012  MachineInstr *LoopDec = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(LoopDecResult);
7013  if (!LoopDec || LoopDec->getOpcode() != ARM::t2LoopDec)
7014  return nullptr;
7015  MachineInstr *LoopStart = nullptr;
7016  for (auto &J : Preheader->instrs())
7017  if (J.getOpcode() == ARM::t2DoLoopStart)
7018  LoopStart = &J;
7019  if (!LoopStart)
7020  return nullptr;
7021  return std::make_unique<ARMPipelinerLoopInfo>(&*I, LoopDec);
7022  }
7023  return nullptr;
7024 }
